---
title: Hold -> Pay -> Confirm -> Broadcast (Spec §15)
---
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User
    participant FE as Frontend
    participant NG as nginx
    participant B as backend-N
    participant RD as Redis
    participant PG as Postgres
    participant OD as OutboxDispatcher
    participant BR as RedisStompBridge
    participant FE2 as Other Frontend (other replica)

    User->>FE: pick seats
    FE->>NG: POST /api/v1/seats/hold
    NG->>B: forward
    B->>RD: EVALSHA token_bucket.lua (rate limit)
    B->>RD: EVALSHA acquire_hold.lua (atomic N keys + cap)
    RD-->>B: OK / SEAT_CONFLICT / CAP_EXCEEDED
    B->>PG: INSERT outbox_events SEAT_HELD<br/>INSERT audit_events HOLD_CREATED
    B-->>FE: 200 {hold_token, ttl=600}

    Note over OD,RD: 200 ms tick (FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED)
    OD->>PG: SELECT undispatched FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED
    OD->>RD: PUBLISH ws.broadcast {SEAT_HELD}
    OD->>PG: UPDATE published_at

    RD-->>BR: ws.broadcast on every replica
    BR->>FE2: STOMP /topic/events/{id}/seats

    User->>FE: pay (mock)
    FE->>NG: POST /api/v1/bookings (Idempotency-Key)
    NG->>B: forward
    B->>RD: GET idem:booking:{user}:{key}
    alt cache hit
        B-->>FE: 200 cached response
    else cache miss
        B->>RD: verify hold token
        B->>PG: BEGIN tx<br/>INSERT bookings<br/>UPDATE seats status<br/>INSERT outbox SEAT_BOOKED<br/>COMMIT
        B->>RD: SET idem:booking:* TTL 24h
        B-->>FE: 201 {bookings[], ticket_pdf_urls[]}
    end

    OD->>RD: PUBLISH ws.broadcast {SEAT_BOOKED}
    BR->>FE2: STOMP push
